        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 7:48PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 748 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Weser to near River Creek Acres. Movement
was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Victoria, Beeville, George West, Goliad, Skidmore, Fannin, Victoria
Colony Creek Country Club, Weesatche, Weser, Nursery, Victoria
Riverside Park, Victoria College, Victoria Mall, Saxet Lakes,
Brentwood Subdivision, Karon, Inez, Salem, Normanna, and Telferner.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 37 between mile markers 54 and 65.
US Highway 281 between mile markers 628 and 632.
US Highway 181 between mile markers 572 and 600.
US Highway 183 between mile markers 628 and 656.
US Highway 59 between mile markers 624 and 722.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 560 and 588.
US Highway 87 between mile markers 798 and 814.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
